## Quick Start

{% if is_nams %}
This project uses **Neo4j Agent Memory Service (NAMS)** — a hosted memory backend. Your `.env` file already contains your API key; the agent reads from and writes to NAMS as you chat with it.

```bash
# Install dependencies
make install

# Edit .env to set OPENROUTER_API_KEY (preferred) or the legacy key for {{ framework_display_name }}
# Then start the application
make start
```

> The graph starts **empty**. Talk to the agent in the chat UI and it will populate memory through use. Want a pre-populated demo with relationships and properties? Re-run the CLI with `--self-hosted --demo`.
{% else %}
