## Agent Framework: {{ framework_display_name }}

Agent model routing is OpenRouter-first by default: `AGENT_PROVIDER=auto`
uses `OPENROUTER_API_KEY` when present, then falls back to this framework's
legacy provider if `AGENT_FALLBACK_PROVIDER=legacy`. Set `AGENT_MODEL` to test
different OpenRouter model slugs without changing code.

{% if framework == 'pydanticai' %}
This project uses [PydanticAI](https://ai.pydantic.dev/) with tool decorators and typed dependencies. The agent is defined in `backend/app/agent.py` using `@agent.tool` decorators for each domain tool. Supports full streaming via `agent.run_stream()`.

To change the LLM model, edit the `Agent(model=...)` parameter in `agent.py`.
{% elif framework == 'claude_agent_sdk' %}
This project uses the [Claude Agent SDK](https://github.com/anthropics/claude-agent-sdk) with a dict-based tool list and an agentic while loop. The agent handles tool calls iteratively until the model stops requesting tools. Supports full streaming via `client.messages.stream()`.

Prefers `OPENROUTER_API_KEY` in `.env`; falls back to `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`.
{% elif framework == 'openai_agents' %}
This project uses the [OpenAI Agents SDK](https://github.com/openai/openai-agents-python) with `@function_tool` decorators and `Runner.run()`. Supports full streaming via `Runner.run_streamed()`.

Prefers `OPENROUTER_API_KEY` in `.env`; falls back to `OPENAI_API_KEY`.
{% elif framework == 'langgraph' %}
This project uses [LangGraph](https://langchain-ai.github.io/langgraph/) with `@tool` decorators and `create_react_agent()`. The agent is a compiled graph that manages tool execution state. Supports full streaming via `graph.astream_events()`.

Prefers `OPENROUTER_API_KEY` in `.env`; falls back to `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` via `langchain-anthropic`.
{% elif framework == 'crewai' %}
This project uses [CrewAI](https://www.crewai.com/) with an Agent/Task/Crew architecture. Tools are decorated with `@tool` and the crew orchestrates execution. Runs synchronously via `asyncio.to_thread()`.

**Note:** CrewAI requires Python 3.11+. Streaming is limited to real-time tool call visualization; text arrives after the crew completes.
{% elif framework == 'strands' %}
This project uses [Strands Agents](https://github.com/strands-agents/strands-agents) with `@tool` decorators and OpenRouter-first model routing. It falls back to Anthropic when configured. Runs synchronously via `asyncio.to_thread()`.

Streaming is limited to real-time tool call visualization; text arrives after the agent completes.
{% elif framework == 'google_adk' %}
This project uses [Google ADK](https://github.com/google/adk-python) with `FunctionTool` wrappers and a Gemini model. The ADK runner manages sessions and tool execution. Supports full streaming via `runner.run_async()`.

Requires a Google Cloud API key or credentials configured for Gemini access.
{% elif framework == 'anthropic_tools' %}
This project uses the [Anthropic API](https://docs.anthropic.com/) directly with a modular `@register_tool` registry and an agentic while loop. Supports full streaming via `client.messages.stream()`.

Prefers `OPENROUTER_API_KEY` in `.env`; falls back to `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`.
{% endif %}

See `backend/app/agent.py` for the full implementation.

